    "notes": "Detection should focus on three high-confidence indicators: (1) auditpol.exe spawned by a non-administrative, non-GPO parent (especially from AppData paths) with /success:disable or /failure:disable arguments; (2) direct registry writes to HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\SysmonDrv\\Parameters by non-SYSTEM processes; (3) registry writes setting HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\WMI\\Autologger\\EventLog-Security\\Enabled to 0. Benign baseline shows auditpol invocations from SYSTEM/GPO chains with enabling arguments, and services.exe making log-size adjustments — differentiate on parent process lineage and argument direction (enable vs. disable)."
